p.d: A head in the stars Fifty years after man first stepped onto the surface of the moon, the astronaut Thomas Pesquet opens the doors to the most fascinating and most dangerous adventure ever attempted by mankind: the conquest of space. With him, Églantine and Jamy experience a whole succession of incredible thrills... Presented by: Jamy Gourmaud, Églantine Émeyé; with Thomas Pesquet. Directed by: Laura Miret, Mathieu Duboscq (France, 2019)
